(# DataPacketInspection Interview Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Project Name:** DataPacketInspection) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**What it is:**) Tj
T*
(DataPacketInspection is a Spring Boot based network inspection platform that helps analyze) Tj
T*
(internet traffic from both offline packet captures and live network activity. It combines) Tj
T*
(packet parsing, traffic classification, firewall correlation, browser activity integration,) Tj
T*
(persistent history, filtering, charting, and role-based access into a single dashboard.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**One-line interview summary:**) Tj
T*
(I built a full-stack network visibility platform in Java Spring Boot that can inspect uploaded) Tj
T*
(PCAP files, monitor live traffic, infer domains and services like YouTube or Instagram, persist) Tj
T*
(analysis history, correlate firewall logs, and enrich packet data with browser activity for) Tj
T*
(deeper user-level context.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Problem Statement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Traditional packet viewers are powerful for analysts, but they are often not friendly for) Tj
T*
(regular users or interview-demo scenarios. Raw network packets alone are also hard to interpret) Tj
T*
(because they mostly show low-level protocol data rather than business-friendly insights.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(I wanted to build a system that answers practical questions such as:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- What traffic is my system generating?) Tj
T*
(- Which source and destination IPs are involved?) Tj
T*
(- Is the traffic allowed or blocked?) Tj
T*
(- Why was it blocked?) Tj
T*
(- Which services are being accessed, like YouTube, Instagram, or Google?) Tj
T*
(- Can I inspect both uploaded traffic logs and live internet traffic?) Tj
T*
(- Can I retain the analysis history for later search and reporting?) Tj
T*
(- Can I enrich network traffic with browser context to understand exact page titles or active) Tj
T*
(URLs?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project was designed as a bridge between a packet analyzer, a network-monitoring) Tj
T*
(dashboard, and an analyst-friendly investigation tool.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Main Objectives) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The application was designed around these major objectives:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Objective 1: Offline packet inspection) Tj
T*
