(   - application hint) Tj
T*
(   - detected host) Tj
T*
(   - host source) Tj
T*
(   - service name) Tj
T*
(   - decision) Tj
T*
(   - reason) Tj
T*
(6. A summary snapshot is generated.) Tj
T*
(7. `HistoryService` stores the session and packet events into the database.) Tj
T*
(8. The snapshot is returned to the dashboard.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.2 Live capture flow) Tj
T*
(1. User selects a network interface.) Tj
T*
(2. `LiveCaptureService` opens the interface in promiscuous mode using `pcap4j`.) Tj
T*
(3. Packets are read continuously in a background executor thread.) Tj
T*
(4. The latest packets are stored in an in-memory deque for live UI updates.) Tj
T*
(5. When capture stops, the in-memory records are persisted as a live capture session.) Tj
T*
(6. The dashboard refreshes periodically and shows the latest events.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.3 History filter flow) Tj
T*
(1. User enters filters such as IP, protocol, decision, host, or service.) Tj
T*
(2. `HistoryApiController` receives the query.) Tj
T*
(3. `HistoryService` builds a dynamic JPA specification.) Tj
T*
(4. The database returns matching packet events.) Tj
T*
(5. The results are transformed back into `PacketRecord` objects.) Tj
T*
(6. The UI renders the filtered results.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.4 Trend chart flow) Tj
T*
(1. The frontend requests trend data for a given time window.) Tj
T*
(2. `HistoryService` loads packet events after a given timestamp.) Tj
T*
(3. Events are grouped by minute.) Tj
T*
(4. Counts are aggregated into `TrafficTrendPoint` objects.) Tj
T*
(5. The dashboard renders a chart-like trend visualization.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.5 Firewall log correlation flow) Tj
T*
(1. An admin uploads a Windows Firewall log.) Tj
T*
(2. `FirewallLogService` parses `DROP` events.) Tj
T*
(3. Each firewall event is stored in the database.) Tj
T*
(4. During packet inspection, the system checks whether a packet matches a firewall `DROP` log) Tj
T*
(entry.) Tj
T*
(5. If it matches, the packet decision is upgraded to `BLOCKED` and the reason reflects the) Tj
T*
(firewall evidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.6 Browser-agent flow) Tj
T*
(1. A Chrome-compatible extension monitors active tabs.) Tj
T*
(2. When the active tab changes or finishes loading, it sends:) Tj
T*
(   - page title) Tj
T*
(   - page URL) Tj
T*
(   - tab ID) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
