() Tj
T*
(## 10. Challenges and How I Solved Them) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Challenge 1: Encrypted traffic hides exact user activity) Tj
T*
(Modern traffic is mostly HTTPS, so exact content is hidden.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Solution:**) Tj
T*
(I added domain/service inference from DNS, HTTP Host, and TLS SNI, and then introduced a) Tj
T*
(browser-agent integration to capture exact page titles and URLs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Challenge 2: Raw packets are hard for users to understand) Tj
T*
(IPs and ports are not user-friendly.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Solution:**) Tj
T*
(I added application hints, service labels, reasons for decisions, saved sessions, and visual) Tj
T*
(summaries.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Challenge 3: Blocked traffic is not always obvious from packets alone) Tj
T*
(A packet capture may not explicitly say that a request was blocked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Solution:**) Tj
T*
(I used multiple signals:) Tj
T*
(- TCP reset) Tj
T*
(- ICMP unreachable) Tj
T*
(- local blocked-port policy) Tj
T*
(- imported Windows Firewall DROP logs) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Challenge 4: Live capture should remain responsive) Tj
T*
(A dashboard can become slow if all captured packets are kept in memory forever.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
